Organization = {Association for Computing Machinery},
Abstract = {The Agave Platform first appeared in 2011 as a pilot project for the
   iPlant Collaborative {[}11]. In its first two years, Foundation saw over
   40\% growth per month, supporting 1000+ clients, 600+ applications, 4
   HPC systems at 3 centers across the US. It also gained users outside of
   plant biology. To better serve the needs of the general open science
   community, we rewrote Foundation as a scalable, cloud native application
   and named it the Agave Platform. In this paper we present the Agave
   Platform, a Science-as-a-Service (ScaaS) platform for reproducible
   science. We provide a brief history and technical overview of the
   project, and highlight three case studies leveraging the platform to
   create synergistic value for their users.},
