   Wuhan Univ; Sci Res Publishing},
Abstract = {Large amount of experts are key asset that universities hold. In order
   to increase people's awareness of experts and foster collaborative
   opportunities, it is necessary to build an expertise repository, which
   enables campus and external users to identify suitable experts and their
   expertise. This paper proposes a methodology for constructing semantic
   repository of academic experts, a Semantic Web application that
   integrates pieces of relevant expertise information from heterogeneous
   data sources. We also demonstrate how to apply visualization techniques
   to visualize the research area of academic experts. Tests on this
   prototype system show that SeRAE supports users browsing and searching
   experts more efficiently and effectively.},
