Year = {1994},
Volume = {36},
Number = {2},
Pages = {87-96},
Abstract = {A specification of an information system using a particular
   computer-aided software engineering (CASE) method describes a particular
   system aspect. The specification can be represented as a population of a
   database schema in a repository supporting the CASE tool. Integrating
   several system aspects requires that their semantic correspondences also
   be determined. The technique presented uses a database schema language
   with deductive capability to capture the semantic correspondences. It
   promises to support multiple CASE tools covering several aspects.
   Semantic correspondence provides insight into why integrating CASE tools
   for large-scale enterprise modelling methods is proving difficult.},
