Note = {Conference on Knowledge and Usage in L2, FRANCE, JUN 29-JUL 01, 2016},
Abstract = {IRIS (iris-database.org) is a freely accessible repository for
   materials, data collection tools, and data used in research on second
   language learning and teaching. Launched in 2011, IRIS now holds nearly
   4,000 files covering a vast spectrum of theoretical, methodological, and
   epistemological perspectives. The current chapter outlines the
   background, purpose, content, and usage of IRIS both generally and as
   within the context of the current volume. We also describe the place of
   IRIS as one of the primary vehicles driving the move toward open science
   practices and replication research in applied linguistics. We conclude
   by encouraging engagement with IRIS from research and practitioners
   alike.},
