   repository for Web users/customers in the context of an application
   model that involves the capturing of eye tracking during the
   user-interface interaction, AJAX-style communication between the client
   and the server, and the conversion of user attention maps to convenient
   data structures. Due to the problem complexity, the client-side
   mechanism for capturing attention nodes were presented in a previously
   published paper, thus the current paper covers strictly the server-side
   details regarding the semantic modeling and programming, with a brief
   presentation of the context, for coherence reasons.},
